[ProMED thanks Mahmoud Orabi for his above submissions.

Bluetongue virus serotype 4 (BTV4), which has been circulating intermittently throughout the Mediterranean basin for decades, is known to be highly pathogenic to susceptible sheep breeds. Cattle, though readily infected by the _Culicoides_ midge vector, undergo -- in most cases of BTV4 infections -- a subclinical course. On the other hand, sheep breeds of the Mediterranean islands, such as the White sheep breed of Mallorca and the Sardinian sheep, are known to be very susceptible with potentially high mortality rates. It is therefore of particular importance to vaccinate the sheep population of the Balearic Islands at the earliest, before the peak of the vector season. - Mod.AS

